--- CREATE METHODS (POST) ---
START HERE IF YOU DID NOT RUN THE SEED SCRIPT
(Creates Parents first)
1. POST http://localhost:3000/api/create/categories
{
"data": {
"category_name": "Computing Devices"
}
}

2. POST http://localhost:3000/api/create/laboratories
{
"data": {
"lab_name": "Advanced Software Lab",
"room_number": "404",
"building": "Tech Tower",
"total_stations": 30
}
}

START HERE IF YOU DID RUN THE SEED SCRIPT
(Uses existing IDs)
3. POST http://localhost:3000/api/create/equipment
{
  "data": {
    "asset_tag": "EQP-2026-002",
    "item_name": "Gaming PC",
    "category_id": 1,
    "brand": "Dell",
    "model": "XPS 8950",
    "serial_number": "SN-DELL-001",
    "specs": {
      "cpu": "Intel i7-12700",
      "cpu_status": "good",
      "ram": "32GB DDR5",
      "ram_status": "bad",
      "storage": "1TB NVMe SSD",
      "storage_status": "good",
      "gpu": "RTX 3060",
      "gpu_status": "good"
    },
    "lab_id": 1,
    "status": "working",
    "purchase_date": "2026-05-09"
  }
}

4. POST http://localhost:3000/api/create/peripherals
{
"data": {
"item_name": "Logitech MX Master 3S",
"category_id": 1,
"brand": "Logitech",
"lab_id": 1,
"working_count": 20,
"damaged_count": 0
}
}

5. POST http://localhost:3000/api/create/borrow_transactions
(instructor_id is auto-filled by JWT, but you can include it if you want)
{
"data": {
"borrower_name": "John Doe",
"equipment_id": 1,
"peripheral_id": null,
"quantity": 1,
"status": "borrowed",
"borrow_date": "2026-05-08",
"expected_return_date": "2026-05-15"
}
}

6. POST http://localhost:3000/api/create/damage_reports
{
"data": {
"equipment_id": 1,
"subject": "Hardware Failure",
"description": "Screen flickering and overheating",
"status": "pending"
}
}

--- UPDATE METHODS (PUT) ---
7. PUT http://localhost:3000/api/update/equipment/1
{
"data": {
"status": "for_repair",
"item_name": "Updated MacBook Name"
}
}

8. PUT http://localhost:3000/api/update/peripherals/1
{
"data": {
"working_count": 15,
"damaged_count": 5
}
}

--- REMOVE & RETRIEVAL METHODS (GET/DELETE) ---
9. GET http://localhost:3000/api/inventory
10. GET http://localhost:3000/api/transactions
11. GET http://localhost:3000/api/reports
12. DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/remove/equipment/1
13. DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/remove/peripherals/1
